&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Airbnb was born in 2007 when two hosts welcomed three guests to their San Francisco home, and has since grown to over 5 million hosts who have welcomed over 2 billion guest arrivals in almost every country across the globe. Every day, hosts offer unique stays and experiences that make it possible for guests to connect with communities in a more authentic way.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The community you will join: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Airbnb, the Growth Marketing team sits at the dynamic crossroads of marketing, engineering, and data science. We’re responsible for driving Airbnb’s business performance by deploying innovative, data-driven marketing strategies.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The difference you will make:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Growth Marketing Lead, you’ll have a unique opportunity to shape Airbnb’s growth narrative in Japan. You’ll be the champion for Growth Marketing channels, translating strategic vision into actionable plans and flawless execution. You’ll identify and prioritize high-impact opportunities, manage complex cross-functional projects, and collaborate with global and regional teams. Your leadership will ensure not only the ongoing success of our core marketing programs, but also the discovery of new areas of growth for your market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and Execute Growth Marketing Strategies: Identify and incorporate local nuances to infuse authentic local flavor into Growth Marketing initiatives, ensuring strategies are tailored to resonate with local cultures, preferences, and market conditions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross-Functional Leadership: Build strong relationships with regional and global teams, setting and managing expectations effectively to deliver measurable business impact. Establish and optimize operating rhythm and ways of working.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project Management: Partner closely with Regional Marketing, Engineering, Product, Data Science, and Creative teams to align on priorities, shape product roadmaps, and lead the planning and execution of Growth Marketing initiatives—ensuring flawless delivery, clear accountability, and effective communication across all levels. Strategic Vision &amp;amp; Hands-On Execution: Operate at both strategic and tactical levels—setting vision, defining KPIs, and rolling up your sleeves to support the execution and optimization of growth campaigns in-market.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Insights &amp;amp; Reporting: Build strong relationships with Japan Business and Marketing Teams and ensure alignment across initiatives. In regional leadership reviews, represent Growth Marketing, provide actionable insights, clear reporting, and thoughtful recommendations to guide strategic decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your expertise: &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Growth Marketing Expertise: 10+ years of&amp;nbsp; relevant work experience in Growth Marketing&amp;nbsp; (Search, CRM, Display, and Affiliate), with proven track record of scaling business for B2C brands ideally in fast-paced, global environments.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Japan Market Mastery: Deep understanding of the Japan market, consumer trends, and digital behaviors, with experience tailoring strategies for Japan and working with local agencies and platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical and Strategic: Expert at leveraging data to prioritize opportunities, drive decision-making, and measure business impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration: Proven ability to influence and drive product conversations with engineering, design, creative and data science partners. Experience working with global channel owners.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project Management Excellence: Highly organized self-starter who thrives in dynamic environments; able to independently manage complex projects from strategy to execution.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stakeholder Management: Exceptional communicator who builds trust and alignment with senior leadership, peers, and global teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Results-Driven: Relentless focus on outcomes, with a track record of delivering against ambitious goals through innovation, iteration, and hands-on execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Acumen: Familiarity with marketing automation, analytics tools, and digital platforms; able to translate business needs into technical requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Commitment To Inclusion &amp;amp; Belonging:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;Airbnb is committed to working with the broadest talent pool possible. We believe diverse ideas foster innovation and engagement, and allow us to attract creatively-led people, and to develop the best products, services and solutions. All qualified individuals are encouraged to apply.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Airbnb was born in 2007 when two hosts welcomed three guests to their San Francisco home, and has since grown to over 5 million hosts who have welcomed over 2 billion guest arrivals in almost every country across the globe. Every day, hosts offer unique stays and experiences that make it possible for guests to connect with communities in a more authentic way.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Community You Will Join:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Homes Supply team is responsible for growing Airbnb’s supply base and ensuring we maintain a diverse, high-quality portfolio of home listings that meet guest expectations for value, variety, and experience. The team also supports hosts globally by enabling efficient planning and execution of growth strategies that align with Airbnb’s mission and resonate with local communities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Difference You Will Make:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you’ll shape the growth and performance of Airbnb’s Homes business across Canada. Leading a team of Market Managers, you’ll drive strategies that expand high-quality supply, strengthen host success across every segment, and enhance the guest experience. You’ll work hand-in-hand with the Country Manager to execute country strategic plans, translating vision into measurable results. Through close collaboration with cross-functional partners, you’ll ensure Airbnb continues to deliver exceptional value to both guests and hosts in every market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Typical Day: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead and inspire&lt;/strong&gt; a team of Market Managers and Market Associates to grow Airbnb’s Homes supply across Canada, expanding partnerships with hosts of all types and driving exceptional business and guest outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner closely with the Country Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to execute country strategic plans, ensuring alignment between local market execution and national business priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Design and execute acquisition strategies&lt;/strong&gt; to bring new, high-quality supply to Airbnb by developing innovative programs, pilots, and local initiatives to reach untapped segments and markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experiment boldly &lt;/strong&gt;to unlock new sources of supply - measure results, refine quickly, and turn proven strategies into playbooks that fuel Airbnb’s growth across Canada and beyond.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Guide territory-level strategies&lt;/strong&gt; for acquisition, optimization, and host quality, directing teams to tailor their approach based on market maturity and host segmentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally&lt;/strong&gt; with Supply Leadership, Marketing, RevOps, Policy, and Product to launch initiatives that improve host performance and accelerate supply growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Monitor and own business performance&lt;/strong&gt;, ensuring markets meet revenue, supply, and quality KPIs while delivering sustainable results that support Airbnb’s broader goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Identify market trends and opportunities&lt;/strong&gt;, providing solutions to overcome barriers and capitalize on emerging demand or regulatory shifts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Coach and develop talent&lt;/strong&gt;, building a high-performing team culture that values experimentation, accountability, and continuous growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Expertise:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;12+ years of experience&lt;/strong&gt; in global operations, business development, or marketplace management, with &lt;strong&gt;5+ years in a people-leadership role&lt;/strong&gt; managing and scaling teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep market expertise and strong understanding of the &lt;strong&gt;Canadian travel and hospitality landscape&lt;/strong&gt;, with experience driving local growth and community engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A combination of &lt;strong&gt;operational&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;and commercial skills&lt;/strong&gt; that will allow you to acquire supply across multiple channels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A &lt;strong&gt;bold, compassionate, and action-oriented leader&lt;/strong&gt; with a &lt;em&gt;strong bias for action&lt;/em&gt; and a proven ability to develop, coach, and empower high-performing teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analytical and strategic thinker&lt;/strong&gt; who uses data and insights to uncover opportunities, shape portfolio strategies, and guide decisions across diverse and evolving markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to &lt;strong&gt;influence product, policy, and cross-functional teams&lt;/strong&gt; to unlock new revenue streams and improve host and market performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled at leveraging tools, dashboards, and analytics to &lt;strong&gt;assess performance, identify trends, and drive accountability.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success in &lt;strong&gt;achieving strong results through others&lt;/strong&gt;, including effective performance management and development of emerging leaders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Known for creating a &lt;strong&gt;positive, driven, and inclusive team culture&lt;/strong&gt; grounded in collaboration, transparency, and continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recognized as a &lt;strong&gt;go-to leader&lt;/strong&gt; who provides clear direction, constructive feedback, and hands-on business coaching to drive both results and professional growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized and adept at &lt;strong&gt;leading multiple initiatives simultaneously&lt;/strong&gt;, turning strategy into action and results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience &lt;strong&gt;growing supply and building partnerships with community and host groups&lt;/strong&gt; is highly valued.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is newly created and does not replace or backfill an existing position.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Location:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is Canada - Remote Eligible. The role may include occasional work at an Airbnb office or attendance at offsites, as agreed to with your manager. While the position is Remote Eligible, you must live in a province where Airbnb Canada, Inc. has a registered entity. Currently we can hire in the following provinces: Ontario, British Columbia, Quebec, and Saskatchewan. This list is continuously evolving, so please check back with your recruiter on what provinces you are eligible to work from.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Commitment To Inclusion &amp;amp; Belonging: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Airbnb is committed to working with the broadest talent pool possible. We believe diverse ideas foster innovation and engagement, and allow us to attract creatively-led people, and to develop the best products, services and solutions. All qualified individuals are encouraged to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We strive to also provide a disability inclusive application and interview process. If you are a candidate with a disability and require reasonable accommodation in order to submit an application, please contact us at: reasonableaccommodations@airbnb.com. Please include your full name, the role you’re applying for and the accommodation necessary to assist you with the recruiting process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We ask that you only reach out to us if you are a candidate whose disability prevents you from being able to complete our online application.&lt;/p&gt;
