&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Airbnb was born in 2007 when two hosts welcomed three guests to their San Francisco home, and has since grown to over 5 million hosts who have welcomed over 2 billion guest arrivals in almost every country across the globe. Every day, hosts offer unique stays and experiences that make it possible for guests to connect with communities in a more authentic way.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Community You Will Join:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The world is changing how it works — it&#39;s moving towards more flexibility for where people can do their jobs. Airbnb has already shown that we can accomplish a lot remotely. Together, we navigated a pandemic, rebuilt our company from the ground up, had a successful IPO, and made 150 upgrades to our product, all over Zoom.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The BizTech Products organization is responsible for delivering innovative technology solutions that empower Airbnb&#39;s internal teams to operate efficiently and effectively. Within BizTech Products, you will join a dynamic team of engineers, architects, and business partners who are passionate about building world-class enterprise systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Technical Lead&lt;/strong&gt;, you will serve as a technical leader and subject matter expert, partnering with senior leadership, cross-functional teams, and external stakeholders to drive strategic initiatives. You will work closely with your manager for thought partnership on strategic priorities while setting best practices for systems engineering across the organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Difference You Will Make:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Technical Lead is a senior technical leader responsible for solving critical problems that require extremely specialized expertise. In this role, you will help deliver and identify the most critical priorities and set best practices for BizTech Products and technical experts in the region.&amp;nbsp; You will be held accountable to deliver on your own Cultural &amp;amp; Functional Excellence (CAFE) contributions and help promote for indirect reports to uphold their CAFE contributions, as these contributions are important for career advancement within Tech.&amp;nbsp; As BizTech’s footprint of regional expertise grows in India, a primary, senior resource to support multiple experts and be accountable for delivering on complex business problems is key.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will serve as a bridge between our current US-based leadership, Airbnb’s global stakeholder community, while utilizing your deep technical skills and enterprise SaaS expertise to architect, optimize, and scale our technology platforms. This includes owning specific, critical enterprise tasks for all of BizTech Products, such as defining when India-based stakeholders should be testing enterprise software changes for acceptance.&amp;nbsp; Your forward-thinking approach and ability to anticipate future needs will significantly accelerate our journey toward becoming an efficient organization centered around self-service, and early adopters of AI.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will act as a leader and innovator in your area of expertise, advising and mentoring others on the team while serving as a liaison between your team and business stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Typical Day:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This role will be hands-on, supporting several in-region resources to ensure that their work is properly prioritized, roadblocks are removed, so that the team can focus to deliver their best work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead architecture designs of complex enterprise systems, ensuring scalability, reliability, and security across the technology stack&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive strategic technology roadmaps by proactively communicating and collaborating with senior leadership and business stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the architecting and migrations from on-premise solutions to cloud environments (Jira, Confluence), including supporting the in-region testing of critical infrastructure, when required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, develop, and optimize integrations, workflows, and automation across enterprise SaaS platforms (Slack, Asana, Jira, Airtable, Workday, and others)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and implement best practices and governance for application access, usage, and data across the organization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive continuous improvement across Airbnb’s application suite, recommending and implementing approved AI tools to foster enhanced self-service and efficiency for Airbnb employees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct analysis of current and future application usage across teams and personas to inform technology decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead business requirements gathering sessions, translating complex business needs into scalable technical solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide mentorship and technical guidance to Systems Engineers &amp;amp; Business Solutions Engineers within BizTech Products India, fostering a culture of continuous learning and innovation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure systems and integrations comply with information security and governance best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current with the latest industry trends in cloud technologies, AI/ML, and enterprise systems to inform strategic direction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help with broader BizTech Engagement activities, ensuring that all India-based employees in India have a voice for engagement and belonging.=&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Expertise:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12+ years of experience as a Systems Engineer, Platform Engineer, or similar role in an enterprise cloud environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of hands-on experience architecting and executing complex migrations from on-premise tools to cloud platforms (with the most critical applications being one or more of:&amp;nbsp; Jira Cloud, Workday, Asana, Slack, AirTable, Miro, RightAnswers, and Figma)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep expertise in enterprise SaaS administration, optimization, and integration across platforms mentioned above&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong coding, automation, and scripting skills with Python, Java and experience with REST APIs, JSON, and integration platforms (Mulesoft, Tray.ai, Workday Studio)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of leading and delivering enterprise-scale projects from inception through successful delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of system architecture, data modeling, integration frameworks, and security best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional problem-solving and analytical skills with the ability to diagnose complex technical issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills with the ability to articulate technical concepts to both technical and non-technical stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience establishing effective partnerships across teams such as fellow BizTech, engineering, security, finance, procurement, and customer support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to Have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with AI/ML integration and automation tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background in IT Service Management (ITSM) frameworks and tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting global, distributed teams across multiple time zones&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of data governance, compliance frameworks, and enterprise security standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with observability and monitoring tools (Datadog, Splunk, New Relic)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Location:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is remote-eligible and can be performed from anywhere in India with a robust internet connection. You will collaborate with teams across multiple time zones, but with a mandatory minimum 2hr overlap with US Pacific Time Zone (8:00am - 10:00am PT) [excluding Fridays, IST].&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of our remote work policy, you may be required to travel periodically for team gatherings, planning sessions, or company events (typically no more than two times per year).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Commitment to Inclusion &amp;amp; Belonging:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Airbnb is committed to working with the broadest talent pool possible. We believe diverse ideas foster innovation and engagement, and allow us to attract creatively-led people, and to develop the best products, services and solutions. All qualified individuals are encouraged to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you need assistance or a reasonable accommodation during the application and recruiting process, please contact us at: &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:reasonableaccommodations@airbnb.com&quot;&gt;reasonableaccommodations@airbnb.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Airbnb was born in 2007 when two hosts welcomed three guests to their San Francisco home, and has since grown to over 5 million hosts who have welcomed over 2 billion guest arrivals in almost every country across the globe. Every day, hosts offer unique stays and experiences that make it possible for guests to connect with communities in a more authentic way.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Community You Will Join:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Our small and extremely capable team of Gurgaon-based colleagues strive to make the impossible happen for our inbound and outbound travelers within this big and diverse market. ACC is providing varied services thereby providing world-class customer experience to our customers. Besides this, ACC is also building deep capabilities for different verticals like Homes, Finance Technology Group, Finance Shared Services, Analytics, etc.&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Difference You Will Make:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The CS Training Business Partner with &lt;em&gt;Community Education, Resolutions and Specializations&lt;/em&gt; focus is an enthusiastic, passionate and flexible team player who will support the CS Training Team to achieve all its priorities. You are a compelling storyteller who can motivate a classroom and communicate ideas using a variety of media, and work as an integral part of the wider CS Org, communicating effectively with cross-functional stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will successfully manage training classrooms for onboarding, upskilling and continued education. You will support our internal and partner teams to be successful through our certification and training quality programs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will take a key part in the world of training projects, as we redefine what training means in the world of Airbnb CS and Trust, and will help incorporate changes and improvements to the CE/R or Specializations curricula under the direction of the CS Training Program Managers and your Lead.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You should be motivated to re-define what training support means for the region and represent regional needs to the global training team and advocate for solutions.&amp;nbsp; You will work closely with local CE/R/Specializations Operations, other Service Excellence teams and regional Partners to coordinate high-level educational projects and provide training in the ever-changing environment of CS.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Finally, you are passionate about the satisfaction, safety and wellbeing of our community, and work tirelessly to ensure they receive the best support Airbnb can provide.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Typical Day:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Regional CS Training Lead, you will be committed to facilitating training that meets the high standards required for our teams. You will collaborate closely with the CS Program Managers to provide impactful and actionable feedback on the training curricula, ensuring that it continually evolves and improves with each delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Training Delivery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitating training, solo or with a co-trainer, following approved curricula&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing the classroom to ensure an organized and productive learning environment for all trainees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring trainee success by providing coaching and feedback during training and providing feedback to leads on trainee engagement and performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keeping up with the day-to-day logistics of running a training, including communicating training details to trainees, coordinating classroom materials, and other administrative duties as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Training Certification&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting with the onboarding of new internal and partner trainers: facilitating orientation sessions and co-delivering trainings as part of our Trainer Certification program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing feedback and coaching to new trainers undergoing Certification, and reporting progress to Training Leads&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Supporting Training Programs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect and analyze feedback for training courses with a continuous improvement mindset; work closely with Program Managers to provide feedback and incorporate meaningful change to enhance future training for relevancy, comprehension, retention, and engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As a Subject Matter Expert, remaining vigilant to identify gaps in knowledge and process, and communicate potential solutions to the appropriate parties&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting with development of ongoing CS education programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Supporting Communication Skills Training Projects&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Undertake assigned communication skills training projects, both regional and global, in collaboration with teammates and stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining up-to-date, functional knowledge of effective communication practices, frameworks, and methodologies, as well as CS tools, systems, and workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting communication skills training assessments for requests and ad hoc requests from key stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Supporting Our Team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting new and seasoned trainers and sharing knowledge within the Training Team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining the position of a role model within the company, as the face of Airbnb and of Airbnb Training to trainees in the classroom and to the wider Airbnb team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Expertise:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-3 Years in Process/Product &amp;amp; Communication Skills/Soft Skills Training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrable interpersonal and cross-functional relationship skills with ability to influence across skip levels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective communication and influencing skills that engage stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Problem solving with measurable outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical thinking and ability to make decisions based on insights and analytics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detail oriented and organized, while also able to think creatively and holistically.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work under conditions of ambiguity in a fast-growth, sometimes uncertain, and complex environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Role model core values to colleagues and learners in how you do your job each day&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong resilience practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Required technical skills: Google Drive Applications, (Mandatory for external and IM)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bonus skills - Adobe Applications (specifically Captivate 8); Rise 360, experience with Absorb is a huge plus!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel may be required - travel restrictions have impacted this recently.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Commitment to Inclusion &amp;amp; Belonging&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Airbnb is committed to working with the broadest talent pool possible. We believe diverse ideas foster innovation and engagement, and allow us to attract creatively-led people, and to develop the best products, services and solutions. All qualified individuals are encouraged to apply.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;How We&#39;ll Take Care of You:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our job titles may span more than one career level. The actual base pay is dependent upon many factors, such as: training, transferable skills, work experience, business needs and market demands. The base pay range shown below is annualized, is inclusive of allowances and is subject to change and may be modified in the future. This role may also be eligible for bonus or incentives, one or more equity programs, benefits, and Employee Travel Credits.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;India Annual Pay Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;₹770,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;₹1,100,000 INR&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Airbnb was born in 2007 when two hosts welcomed three guests to their San Francisco home, and has since grown to over 5 million hosts who have welcomed over 2 billion guest arrivals in almost every country across the globe. Every day, hosts offer unique stays and experiences that make it possible for guests to connect with communities in a more authentic way.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Community You Will Join:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join the Global Operations Training team. We support frontline teams and prepare them to best serve our customers. We are a global team with expertise in training design, development, delivery, and organizational development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our mission is to empower everyone to deliver exemplary service through continuous and impactful learning. We work closely with Delivery and Optimization, Change Management, Service Enablement, Process Improvement, Quality, Analytics, Policy, and many other teams!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Difference You Will Make:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Training Coordinator, you will play a vital role in supporting our tactical training operations, with a primary focus on vendors and region-specific markets. You will work closely with the Training Partner Managers, acting as an internal Airbnb point of contact for our growing network of partner trainers, supporting them with questions and concerns, channeling feedback to the appropriate teams within Airbnb and supporting the execution of a wide array of training operations exercises.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be successful in this role, you must have the ability to interact with staff (at all levels) in a fast-paced environment, demonstrate excellent organization and attention to detail, and remain flexible, proactive, resourceful and efficient. Day-to-day activities may include collection, organizing, scheduling, monitoring and distributing information across our internal and external global CS network. Your passion for operational excellence, coupled with strong interpersonal skills, will ensure our teams remain organized and effective.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Typical Day:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as an internal Airbnb POC, supporting vendors and channeling questions and feedback to appropriate teams within Airbnb, including Service Delivery Partner Optimization, Workforce Management, Knowledge Management and Quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and preserve trusted relationships through clear and direct communication, collaboration and delegation across multiple levels, internally and externally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate the logistics of internal new hire training by working closely with Talent, Recruiting and the Learning Facilitation Team Manager.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and drive vendor trainer engagement initiatives, including organizing and moderating regular meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure training performance documentation is accessible, completed correctly and in full, and conduct regular audits to ensure required maintenance is addressed in a timely manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support with troubleshooting technical issues and driving completion of critical projects.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Expertise:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with training operations and third-party vendors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organization, attention to detail, flexibility, proactivity&amp;nbsp; and resourcefulness.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preferred knowledge of Tableau, SQL and other Airbnb databases, including creating queries and manipulating large data sets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preferred familiarity with Absorb (LMS) and Orchestra (TMS).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and interpersonal skills, with a proven track record of&amp;nbsp; the ability to work across departments and levels.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adaptability to quickly adjust to new technologies, business needs and workload reprioritization.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Willingness to travel, if necessary (up to 25%).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Location: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is Canada - Remote Eligible. The role may include occasional work at an Airbnb office or attendance at offsites, as agreed to with your manager. While the position is Remote Eligible, you must live in a province where Airbnb Canada, Inc. has a registered entity. Currently we can hire in the following provinces: Ontario, British Columbia, Quebec, and Saskatchewan. This list is continuously evolving, so please check back with your recruiter on what provinces you are eligible to work from.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Commitment To Inclusion &amp;amp; Belonging: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Airbnb is committed to working with the broadest talent pool possible. We believe diverse ideas foster innovation and engagement, and allow us to attract creatively-led people, and to develop the best products, services and solutions. All qualified individuals are encouraged to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We strive to also provide a disability inclusive application and interview process. If you are a candidate with a disability and require reasonable accommodation in order to submit an application, please contact us at: reasonableaccommodations@airbnb.com. Please include your full name, the role you’re applying for and the accommodation necessary to assist you with the recruiting process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We ask that you only reach out to us if you are a candidate whose disability prevents you from being able to complete our online application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;We use automated tools to help our recruiting team efficiently screen a large volume of applications. All final hiring decisions are made by a human reviewer.&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;This role is for an existing vacancy within the organization.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;How We&#39;ll Take Care of You:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Our job titles may span more than one career level. The actual base pay is dependent upon many factors, such as: training, transferable skills, work experience, business needs and market demands. The base pay range shown below is annualized, is subject to change and may be modified in the future. This role may also be eligible for bonus, equity, benefits, and Employee Travel Credits.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Canada Annual Pay Range&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$67,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$79,000 CAD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;Airbnb was born in 2007 when two hosts welcomed three guests to their San Francisco home, and has since grown to over 5 million hosts who have welcomed over 2 billion guest arrivals in almost every country across the globe. Every day, hosts offer unique stays and experiences that make it possible for guests to connect with communities in a more authentic way.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Difference You Will Make:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Workforce Management (WFM) Scheduler is vital in ensuring we have the best possible support for our guests and hosts within Customer Support operations. As the Customer Support scheduler, you will be responsible for the allocation of headcount across multiple sites, channels and tiers and be expected to manage these and the relationships with partner WFM teams. You would be an important part of a fast moving and high profile team and be required to work closely with cross-functional teams to achieve the best results.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Typical Day: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with operations to generate and deploy schedules based on language, skill and contact channel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set up, manage and maintain schedules for several internal teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage, build and track/report schedule demand for multiple partner sites with multiple channels and languages across a shared queue environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and run scheduling scenarios and provide analysis of potential impacts of new lines of business, changes to SLA, routing, skilling etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the broader Workforce Management (WFM) team to understand all aspects of capacity planning and forecasting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track, analyse and report employee performance with reports from Genesys&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyse and report historical data and trends, daily, weekly, monthly etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyse performance data to identify opportunities to operate more effectively and efficiently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effectively communicate across the broader Airbnb team and our outsource partners, including preparing performance reporting and the delivery of them at WBR/MBR and QBR’s.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #000000;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Expertise:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s Degree or equivalent experience is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have a minimum 5 years of experience in a contact center management role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Genesys WFM (preferred) or similar applications (i.e. IEX/NICE, Aspect/eWFM) is a must&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Well-developed problem-solving and analytical skills with attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to effectively communicate complex information clearly to a non WFM/technical audience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to Interactive Insights, Tableau and SQL preferred&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Eagerness to learn &amp;amp; manage multiple technical systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to process large amounts of complex raw data and present in a comprehensible fashion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated and driven, used to being in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
